## Problems (must fix — these are the unfinished v2 items, now unblocked)
1. **Wire real stems into the engine.** AudioEngine currently SYNTHESIZES per-stem oscillators from `synthKey`. Replace the load path with fetch+`decodeAudioData` of the real mp3 stems into AudioBuffers (drop synthesis for these songs). Keep mixer routing (gain/pan/mute/solo) against the decoded buffers.
2. **Rewrite `songs.js`** with the 3 real songs: real title/bpm/key, real stem file lists, and section/cue timings that match the actual tracks (not the old 8-bar synth math). Use the Click stem for count-in and Guide for the guide-cue track.
3. **Reconcile stem count to the 6-channel mixer.** Songs have 6-10 stems; map to the strips consistently (e.g. Drums, Bass, Guitar(s), Keys/Piano, Synths/Organ, Vocals; fold Perc/2nd guitar where needed; Click→count-in, Guide→cue track or its own strip). Keep it identical across songs so the UI is stable.
4. **Transcode/trim before shipping (size gate).** Raw stems are far too heavy for GitHub Pages (~200MB+). Transcode to ~96kbps mono and/or trim each stem to a loop-aligned ~60-90s clip. Target total demo audio well under ~40MB. Output to `public/demos/audio-software-engineer-needed-for/stems/<song-slug>/`.
5. **Rebuild + copy.** `npm run build` in `demo-src` (base `/demos/audio-software-engineer-needed-for/`), copy `dist/*` into the public demo dir, confirm it loads with no console errors and real audio plays.
6. **Write `demo-builder2.out`** with a handoff so deploy + deploy-test can run. Commit is deploy's job, but the build must pass first. Per the request, media-capture and proposal-writer do NOT rerun — only re-verify the demo end to end after the swap.

No earlier step needs redoing — plan/research are fine; this is purely execution that stopped at the download stage twice. Looping to demo-builder.

